## Known Findings (do NOT repeat — find NEW issues)

- F-001: Dinero withdrawal finalization condition is inverted (High, high)
- F-002: Morpho market oracle uses account-agnostic vault price and can misprice pending-withdraw collateral (High, medium)
- F-003: LP zero-balance legs create missing withdraw requests that break pending valuation and finalization (Medium, high)
- F-004: Reward debt is advanced even when reward transfer fails (Medium, high)
- F-005: Zero-yield-token withdraw requests can trigger division-by-zero on finalization accounting (Low, medium)
- F-007: Ethena zero-duration cooldown mode strands redeemed USDe in cloned holder (Medium, high)
- F-008: Dinero withdrawals never request validator exits (Low, medium)
- F-009: Dinero request-id nonce overflows after 65,535 withdrawals and halts new requests (Low, high)
- F-010: Router transfer authorization is not bound to the intended source account (Low, medium)
- F-011: Any whitelisted lending router can delete another router's live position record (Low, high)
- F-012: Sequencer outage protection is skipped on legacy oracle accessors (Low, low)
- F-013: Permissionless manual finalization can lock in GenericERC4626 withdrawals early and strip later share appreciation (Medium, high)
- F-014: Partial redemption of finalized tokenized withdraw requests can strand permanent rounding dust (Low, high)
- F-015: Executed proxy upgrade state is not cleared, allowing potential same-implementation `executeUpgrade` replay (Low, low)
- F-016: Curve V2 liquidation precheck can make LP vault positions unliquidatable (High, high)
- F-017: Account reward updates use stale accumulator values after vault reward claims (Medium, high)
- F-018: Force-claim delay enables just-in-time deposits to capture already-accrued pool rewards (Low, medium)
- F-019: Reward-pool migration can claim old-pool rewards without allocating them to users (Medium, high)
- F-020: Curve ETH-leg async withdraw uses address(0) manager key after ETH is wrapped to WETH (Medium, high)
- F-021: Ethena pending-withdraw valuation prices fixed USDe claim as yield-bearing sUSDe (Medium, high)
- F-022: Dinero finalization credits nominal upxETH amounts instead of measured redeemed ETH (Low, low)
- F-023: Dinero request IDs encode unbounded batch ranges that must be fully looped on finalization (Low, medium)
- F-024: Morpho migration can be underfunded by borrow-share rounding (Low, medium)

